STREETS in a Scottish seaside town have cordoned off for hours as police negotiators try to prevent a man from self-harming after he barricaded himself in a room.
Officers raced to the Short Stay Hostel, Princes Street, Ardrossan at 11.50 last night following reports of a disturbance.
They found a man holed up in a room at the hostel threatening to injure himself.
Specially trained officers including public order officers and licensed force negotiators are currently at the scene.
There are no reports of anyone else within the room.
